bio.experienceSummary:
As a caregiver, my passion lies in nurturing the growth and development of young minds. Through my previous babysitting experiences, I've discovered an innate ability to connect with children and foster a positive impact on their lives.

My patient and calm nature allows me to create a serene environment for children to thrive. My creativity and imagination shine through as I engage them in a variety of games and activities, both educational and fun. I firmly believe in open communication with parents and provide regular updates on their child's day, using their preferred method of communication.

With a year of experience under my belt, I'm comfortable caring for one child at a time and am happy to assist with tasks such as cooking, light housekeeping, and travel. As a Certified Nursing Assistant, I possess the necessary training and skills to provide exceptional care for children.

I've grown up in a dance studio where I would have to assist/teach kids of multiple ages. I have experience with picking kids up from school, and taking them to where they need to be. I cook for them, clean up after them, help them with their homework. I keep them busy and out of trouble. Very infant friendly and a super warm hearted caring person

I'm used to caring for more than one child at a time, preparing meals, helping with homework, giving baths, reading stories and putting children to sleep. I'm also fully vaccinated with booster and CPR/First Aid Certified.

description.originalText: Tayla was great with my elderly mother. She was patient, on time and built a bond with my mother. I hired Tayla for a week while I was away on vacation. She assisted with baths, doctors appointment, medication, keeping my mother company, etc. Iâ€™ll definitely hire her again!

bio.experienceSummary: Hi, my name is Gricelda. I have 10 years of experience. I am bilingual. I am CPR/First aid training certified. I have my CDA certificate. I have the experience to care for more than once child at once. I can help with Light Housekeeping, children laundry, and tidying up them. I consider myself a trustworthy, responsible, caring, and honest person. I want to be able to provide parents with comfort and security of having someone trustworthy watching their children.

description.originalText: Absolutely amazing to work with. She is attentive, loving, punctual and very gentle with my little one. I highly recommend her .

bio.experienceSummary: Hello! I'm Kerene, a dedicated nanny with over 5 years of experience in childcare and a passion for nurturing young minds. I began my professional journey in 2014, outside of caring for my younger siblings since they were babies, and now they are aged 8, 10, and 13. Alongside my role as a teacher assistant, I've honed my skills in organizing activities, preparing meals, bedtime stories, and even teaching a bit of French. Creating a safe, structured, and loving environment where children can thrive brings me immense joy. I look forward to bringing my experience, positivity, and genuine care to your family!

description.displayText: This review is long overdue! From our first phone call, I knew Kerene was the one. Not only is she punctual, dependable and responsible, but she is so very loving and attentive to our 2 young children. She became family from day 1. My children loved all the fun adventures they went on and always came home with a story. Never a dull moment. I knew my children were in the best care and never had to worry leaving them. She also helped keep the home neat and prepared meals when needed. Kerene is an absolute God sent!

bio.experienceSummary: Hello, My name is Kiara. I am currently a college student and I am looking to work Part-time or Full-time. I enjoy children a lot being that I have a lot of younger family members, so I was always designated as the "go-to sitter". I have an open availability and I am willing to help out! My favorite things to do are arts and crafts, read, listen to music and most all enjoy the outdoor weather! I have my own car so transportation would never be a problem, I am ready to start whenever you need me!

description.displayText: My little one loved spending time with Kiara. She was always on time and completely dependable. I recommend her to anyone.

bio.experienceSummary:
Hello!

I am a 28-year-old mom of one to a 10-year-old. I am new to Staten Island but also to New York. I have just relocated to be with my boyfriend who is a Sergeant in NYPD. Together we have 3 children ages 4, 9, and 10. I also have recent experience with infants as a surrogate mother and was fortunate enough to have cared for this child for two months. 

In my free time I enjoy running outside and feeling fresh air on my face, reading as many books as I possibly can, and I love to paint. 

I am looking for full time employment but could be open to part time as well. I am passionate about family values and spending time with children giving them undivided attention. 

I am open to a nanny setting where I come in the house care for children, help with cooking, cleaning, prepping for school or sports or anything that is going on. I am available to provide transportation as needed. We will enjoy time at home, along with any additional extracurriculars and/or approved outings.

I have experience with all children ages and experience with boys and girls. I worked as a caregiver for five years in a kindergarten/daycare with newborns and kids up to 6 years old, including children with special needs. 

I consider myself a very motivated person, independent, communicative, organized, honest, open minded, flexible, mature, responsible and hardworking. I have my own car. Non-smoking.

I have a flight attendant course and certificate of CPR. 

Please let me know if you have interest. I look forward to hearing from you!

description.displayText:
I don't have anything to complain about her. I really recommend Gabby to any family, she is punctual, flexible (always there when I needed some help with my baby), lovely and mature. 
She took care of my 7 months old baby for a few weekends and I really appreciate her work.
